### Network Capture During Authentication

Script to trigger authentication and capture:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# Start packet capture in background
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 port 88 -w auth_capture.pcap &
TCPDUMP_PID=$!

# Wait for capture to start
sleep 2

# Trigger authentication (various methods)
# Method 1: SMB connection
net use \\\\192.168.1.10\\share /user:domain\\user password

# Method 2: RDP connection
rdesktop -u domain\\user -p password 192.168.1.10

# Method 3: Web authentication with Negotiate
curl -N --negotiate --user user:password http://192.168.1.100

# Wait for traffic
sleep 5

# Stop capture
kill $TCPDUMP_PID
```

